 be here until next week.  There is still a lot of coordination and management type stuff to do before we&#8217;re ready to release.</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 04 Dec 2008 00:29:20 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Ryan";}s:7:"summary";s:698:"<p>As announced on the wordpress.com blog, 2.7 is coming to wordpress.com tomorrow.  Actually, 2.7 has been running on wordpress.com for awhile, just not the exciting new admin UI.  Here&#8217;s a peek at what the admin will look like on wordpress.com.</p>\n<p><a title="WordPress.com 2.7 Preview by ryancboren, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/ryanboren/3080433013/"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3212/3080433013_2059b812ee.jpg" alt="WordPress.com 2.7 Preview" width="500" height="322" /></a></p>\n<p>The final release of 2.7 won&#8217;t be here until next week.  There is still a lot of coordination and management type stuff to do before we&#8217;re ready to release.</p>";}i:24;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:25:"Matt: Open Source Economy";s:4:"guid";s:41:"http://ma.tt/2008/12/open-source-economy/";s:4:"link";s:41:"http://ma.tt/2008/12/open-source-economy/";s:11:"description";s:296:"<p><a href="http://whurley.com/2008/12/03/three-reasons-open-source-will-save-the-economy/">Three Reasons Open Source Will Save The Economy</a>. Only three? I bet we could think of way more. <img src="http://ma.tt/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 03 Dec 2008 22:55:54 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Matt";}s:7:"summary";s:296:"<p><a href="http://whurley.com/2008/12/03/three-reasons-open-source-will-save-the-economy/">Three Reasons Open Source Will Save The Economy</a>. Only three? I bet we could think of way more. <img src="http://ma.tt/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>";}i:25;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:74:"Lorelle on WP: WordPress 2.7 Hits WordPress.com Thursday, December 4, 2008";s:4:"guid";s:36:"http://lorelle.wordpress.com/?p=3310";s:4:"link";s:96:"http://lorelle.wordpress.com/2008/12/02/wordpress-27-hits-wordpresscom-thursday-december-4-2008/";s:11:"description";s:6346:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><p><a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/tag/wordpress-news/" title="WordPress News"><img src="http://lorelle.files.wordpress.com/2007/01/wpnews1.png" alt="WordPress News" align="right" /></a>In an announcement on the <a href="http://www.wordpress.com/" title="WordPress.com free blogs" rel="tag">WordPress.com</a> blog, <a href="http://en.blog.wordpress.com/2008/12/03/27-gets-here-in-two-days/" title="WordPress 2.7 Gets Here in Two Days">WordPress 2.7 will arrive on Thursday, December 4, 2008,</a> at 8PM Eastern Time in the United States. </p>\n<p>The article also includes instructions on what to expect on WordPress.com from the new features and instructions on using the new Administration Panel interface, though most of it is really user friendly and intuitive.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/development/2008/12/wordpress-27-release-candidate-1/" title="WordPress 2.7 Release Candidate 1">WordPress 2.7 Release Candidate 1</a> was released December 1, with <a href="http://trac.wordpress.org/timeline?from=12%2F01%2F08&amp;daysback=16&amp;changeset=on&amp;update=Update" title="280 commits">280 commits</a> since WordPress 2.7 beta 3. This release includes the new menu icons created by the <a href="http://wordpress.org/development/2008/11/the-results-of-project-icon/" title="The Results of Project Icon">winners</a> of <a href="http://wordpress.org/development/2008/11/wordpress-27-project-icon/" title="Project Icon">WordPress 2.7: Project Icon</a>, and fixes to the browser bugs that have been giving the development team headaches.</p>\n<p>Testing is in high drive if <a href="http://www.wordpress.com/" title="WordPress.com free blogs" rel="tag">WordPress.com</a> will have WordPress 2.7 on board in two days. This could mean that the full version of WordPress should be released just before or at the same time. Originally, WordPress.com bloggers were told by Matt Mullenweg and Jane Wells of <a href="http://www.automattic.com/" title="Automattic - parent company of WordPress, WordPress.com, Akismet, BuddyPress, and more" rel="tag">Automattic</a> that WordPress.com bloggers would see WordPress 2.7 about two weeks after the full version launch. Unless WordPress.com will be testing the new version before the full version launch, be ready to install WordPress 2.7 by the weekend.</p>\n<p>Cheers and good thoughts to all the hearty developers and testers not getting any sleep to ensure the deadline is met. This is really going to be one of the best versions of WordPress.</p>\n<p>For a glimpse of some of the new features, see <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/2008/11/27/wordpress-27-release-news-and-links/" title="WordPress 2.7 Release News and Links">WordPress 2.7 Release News and Links</a>.</p>\n<p><img src="http://lorelle.files.wordpress.com/2006/08/sig.gif" alt="" /><br />\n<hr />\n<p><font size="-1"><b>Site Search Tags:</b> <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/index.php?s=wordpress+2.7" rel="tag">wordpress 2.7</a>, <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/index.php?s=wordpressdotcom" rel="tag">wordpressdotcom</a>, <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/index.php?s=wordpresscom" rel="tag">wordpresscom</a>, <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/index.php?s=wordpress.com" rel="tag">wordpress.com</a>, <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/index.php?s=wordpress+2.7" rel="tag">wordpress 2.7</a>, <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/index.php?s=wordpress+release" rel="tag">wordpress release</a>, <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/index.php?s=wordpress+news" rel="tag">wordpress news</a>, <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/index.php?s=wordpress+version" rel="tag">wordpress version</a>, <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/index.php?s=wordpress" rel="tag">wordpress</a>, <a href="http://lorelle.wordpress.com/index.php?s=wordpress+development" 